
#https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/1.1.x/quickstart/
1-The next the light bulb, you see the red lines click on it to install
2-To install a package in window, go to File/settings/your project/python 
interpreter/click+ button/Type the name of the package/
3-To the terminal/ pip install Flask 
example of Flask App
hello.py
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)


@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return 'Hello, World!'

To run Flask application, we need to create evironment variable
1- set FLASK_APP=hello.py     //hello.py is the name our project

with window PowerShell

$env:FLASK_APP ="hello.py"
python -m flask run 
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Instead of using command line 
$env:FLASK_APP="hello.py"
python -m flask run 

#we use the following to start our project in the main.py 
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

print(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello_world():
    return 'Hello, World! of python'


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()

and click on just run on main.py just normal python execution code to the server address and we 
dont need ctrl + c to stop the programm,e just click on the stop button 
from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello_world():
    return 'Hello, World! of python'


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
 from flask import Flask

app = Flask(__name__)

@app.route('/')
def hello():
    return "Good Morning"

@app.route('/bye')
def bye():
    return "Good Bye"

if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run()
